You might want to implement custom common interface, containing `log()` method:

````java
public interface LoggingException {
    void log();
}
````

And implement your exceptions from it:

````java
public class MyException extends RuntimeException implements LoggingException {
    public void log() {
        System.out.println(&quot;Logging MyException&quot;);
    }
}
````

Note: it is not a common practice to add custom functionality to exceptions, especially logging. You might want to use logger externally and do something like this:

````java
catch(Exception e) {
    log.error(&quot;error happened&quot;, e);
}
````

